SA lockdown day 18 in South Africa. eNCA Tshegohaco Moagi, is out in the streets of Johannesburg to give us an update, and reporter Monique Mortlock is in Cape Town. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - No new deaths have been recorded as the number of infections continues to increase. Twenty-five people have died from the coronavirus in South Africa where the number of confirmed cases stands at 2,173. READ: Coronavirus intensive care - what is involved? More than 80,000 tests have been conducted. The Department said they are seeing an increase in tests conducted at public laboratories, of the 5, 032 tests conducted in the past day, 3, 192 were done in public laboratories. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.